§ Why ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ Once we have a notion of distance, we can define a more
    general notion of convergence. ⦉
⦉

§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ Let $(X, d)$ be a metric space and let $(x_n)_{n ∈ 𝗡}$ be
    a sequence in $X$. ⦉

  ‖ A ❬limit❭ of $(x_n)_{n ∈ 𝗡}$ is an element $x ∈ X$ for
    which $d(x, x_n) → 0$. ⦉
⦉

